data.description:
Welcome to your next home! This 4 bedroom/ 3 bath brick home is located in the heart of Destin, right off of highly desired Indian Trail.  Tucked into a cul-de-sac within Eagles Landing subdivision, this home offers a retreat while being conveniently situated to access all the entertainment that Destin provides! As you enter the home you are greeted with an open concept flow between the dining room, living room, and into the kitchen. The area is decorated in light coastal colors with farmhouse details setting a tone of casual comfort. From the entryway your eyes follow the wood styled tile floor into the dining area on your right. The dining room is spacious enough to accommodate a large table with a buffet cabinetry built into the far wall. The living room has a custom entertainment focal wall with shaker style cabinetry and natural wood details. The gas fireplace, trimmed in light toned tiles, will keep you warm on chilly winter evenings. The galley style kitchen features a breakfast bar, breakfast nook, farmhouse sink trimmed with gold hardware, and bright white quartz countertops. 

The ranch style home features a split floor plan with the master bedroom and ensuite bath on the West side and the three guest bedrooms situated on the East side. The master bedroom is roomy and allows beautiful light in from the large window on the backside of the home. The ensuite bathroom has a double sink vanity, separate shower and garden tub, and a walk-in closet.

The guest bedrooms are located down hallway located off the living room. The first room on the front of the home is decorated in shabby chic colorful pops with a tortoiseshell chandelier. This room shares a full jack-and-jill style bathroom connecting it with the middle guest room. The middle room is decorated in coastal colors and accented with a light farmhouse wood beaded chandelier. On the backside of the home is a full bathroom leading to the third guest bedroom. This room has a beautiful farmhouse styled focal wall and bright view into the backyard. 

Enjoy the privacy of your backyard which backs up to a natural preserve. You can unwind by the pool or from the serenity of your screened in back porch.  This space is a perfect retreat to enjoy the beautiful Florida weather and escape from the hustle of daily routines. 

If the house is not enough on its own, you can take advantage of the community's pool and picnic area. Additionally, there are several paths throughout Eagles landing and onto Indian trail to explore!
